#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:29
msgid ""
"The Moderation team is a special case where being a member demands high "
"community trust and performing difficult work, and the work that the "
"Moderation team does always needs a seat at the Leadership Council table, "
"even though they are also small."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:31
msgid ""
"Additionally, out of the small number of crates.io team members, many either "
"do not have bandwidth to serve on the Leadership Council or would have "
"perceived conflicts of interest (namely, being employed by the Rust "
"Foundation) that don't make them the best candidate for Leadership Council "
"representative."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:33
msgid ""
"This RFC is not proposing any sort of requirement such as \"top-level teams "
"must have subteams\", necessarily (proposing such a requirement is left as "
"an exercise for a future RFC). Pointing out the Crates.io team is the only "
"top-level team without subteams is merely one signal that the Crates.io team "
"isn't comparable to the other top-level teams."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:35
msgid ""
"[RFC 3392](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/blob/master/text/3392-"
"leadership-council.md#top-level-teams) outlines what typically qualifies a "
"team as \"top-level\". While one could make the argument that the Crates.io "
"team fits these points, there are arguably two aspects where it does not "
"neatly fit:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:37
msgid ""
"\"Have a purview that not is a subset of another team's purview\": this is "
"hard to argue exactly as most teams don't have well defined purviews, but "
"one could argue that Crates.io's purview is a subset of multiple teams' (see "
"the \"Alternatives\" section for discussion on this point)."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:39
msgid ""
"\"Be the ultimate decision-makers on all aspects of that purview\": Many "
"decisions involving the crates.io team are ultimately one or more of:"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:40
msgid "legal decisions or funding work done by the Foundation"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:41
msgid "hosting decisions made by Infrastructure"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:42
msgid "capabilities that interface with Cargo"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:44
msgid ""
"While the Crates.io team is certainly involved in those decisions and in "
"executing them, it's arguable whether the Crates.io team is the ultimate "
"decision-maker of all aspects of running crates.io."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:46
msgid ""
"In the past, whether a team is \"top-level\" or not has not been of huge "
"consequence. However, this is no longer true since [RFC 3392](https://github."
"com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/3392) introduced the Leadership Council whose "
"representation is based on top-level team status. RFC 3392 specifically "
"called out the need for re-examination of which teams are top-level, and "
"this proposal is the second attempt at such a re-examination, after [RFC "
"3533](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/pull/3533) that moved the Release "
"team under the Infrastructure team."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:48
msgid ""
"Currently, the representation burden is not productive or fair: by virtue of "
"the Crates.io team being small, more of the teams' collective time is being "
"spent on being a representative of the Leadership Council. Additionally, the "
"Crates.io Leadership Council representative is speaking for fewer people "
"than other teams' representatives are."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:50
msgid ""
"For the purposes of actual decision making, the Crates.io subteam retains "
"all decision-making power with regard to crates.io related issues (i.e., "
"this proposal does not change who makes any particular decision and is "
"purely a change in Council representation). This may change over time should "
"the Dev tools team choose to structure itself in a different way."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:52
msgid "Practicalities"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:54
msgid ""
"Once this proposal is accepted, the Crates.io team will move to be a subteam "
"of Dev tools. The Dev tools team does not change its top-level form."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:56
msgid ""
"The Dev tools team's Council representative would continue to serve on the "
"Council while the Crates.io representative would immediately stop counting "
"as a representative for all purposes.[^plan]"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:58
msgid ""
"It is currently the unofficial plan that Carol Nichols will step down in her "
"role as the Crates.io representative, and Eric Huss would take over as the "
"rep, but this would be made official after the merger through internal Dev "
"tools team process."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:60
msgid "Alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:62
msgid "Merge Crates.io into Infrastructure"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:64
msgid ""
"Crates.io uses infrastructure such as Fastly, CloudFront, S3, Heroku, "
"GitHub, and other services that are managed by the Infrastructure team. "
"There's certainly an argument to be made that the Crates.io team belongs "
"there, however, the docs.rs team is in a similar situation and they are a "
"subteam of Dev tools."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:66
msgid "Be a subteam of both Dev tools and Infra"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:68
msgid ""
"The Types team provides precedence for this; technically the Types team is a "
"subteam of both the Compiler and Lang teams. However, the teams repo doesn't "
"really support multiple inheritance. The Crates.io team would like to "
"cultivate a closer relationship with the Cargo team especially, and thinks "
"the relationship with the Infra team could be continued in the current "
"manner."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:70
msgid "Creating a new team"
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:72
msgid ""
"There are aspects of the Crates.io Team's purview that are more policy "
"decisions than they are implementation details, such as what information "
"Crates.io should surface about each crate, how to handle different crate "
"ownership situations, or what browsers the site should support."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:74
msgid ""
"There could be a new team dedicated to policy questions such as these and "
"other questions that have currently come up to the Leadership Council. "
"People who enjoy thinking about and discussing policies might enjoy being on "
"this team and not being responsible for implementing the policies. People "
"implementing the policies might enjoy not being responsible for creating the "
"policies."
msgstr ""

#: src/3595-move-crates-io-team-under-dev-tools.md:76
msgid ""
"However, it isn't clear if a policy team would be feasible and desirable. If "
"so, this division could be done as a future enhancement; this RFC does not "
"prevent such."
msgstr ""

